# Action Items

- [ ] Review and prioritize tasks

- [ ] [HIGH] Adopt a Hybrid/Lease-First Strategy: Prioritize leasing or cloud-based consumption models initially to minimize upfront CAPEX and maximize runway for Series A preparation. (Owner: CEO, Due: TBD)
- [ ] [HIGH] Implement a Phased Infrastructure Rollout: Allocate capital based on validated demand from pilot customers, ensuring that GPU procurement is triggered only when scaling requirements demonstrably exceed current leased capacity. (Owner: CEO, Due: TBD)
- [ ] [HIGH] Integrate Compute into the Product Roadmap: Mandate that all future feature development prioritizes scalable, flexible infrastructure (e.g., cloud services) to ensure rapid iteration and competitive responsiveness. (Owner: CEO, Due: TBD)
- [ ] [HIGH] Establish Clear Exit Criteria for Asset Ownership: Define specific performance benchmarks (e.g., utilization rates, ROI on compute) that must be met before considering large-scale asset purchases versus ongoing leasing agreements. (Owner: CEO, Due: TBD)
- [ ] [HIGH] Engage CFO/CTO for Joint Modeling: Require a joint financial model to assess the Total Cost of Ownership (TCO) across both leasing and purchasing options, factoring in potential future scaling demands. (Owner: CEO, Due: TBD)
- [ ] [HIGH] Prioritize Leasing for Initial Scaling: Recommend pursuing a lease or subscription model for initial compute needs to preserve working capital and maximize runway for customer acquisition efforts. (Owner: CFO, Due: TBD)
- [ ] [HIGH] Develop a Phased Purchase Strategy: Allocate capital for asset purchase only once clear, multi-year revenue projections (post-Series A) validate the sustained need for ownership versus ongoing operational costs. (Owner: CFO, Due: TBD)
- [ ] [HIGH] Model the Series A Impact: Calculate how upfront hardware costs impact the valuation multiples sought in the upcoming funding round. High CapEx may dilute the perceived ROI unless growth forecasts are extremely aggressive. (Owner: CFO, Due: TBD)
- [ ] [HIGH] Negotiate Flexible Contracts: If purchasing is deemed necessary, negotiate lease-like terms (e.g., subscription models with exit clauses) to mitigate long-term vendor lock-in risk. (Owner: CFO, Due: TBD)
- [ ] [MEDIUM] Adopt a Hybrid Phased Strategy: Start by heavily leveraging cloud leasing (AWS/Azure/GCP) for MVP deployment and scaling, minimizing upfront CAPEX risk while validating product-market fit. (Owner: CTO, Due: TBD)
- [ ] [MEDIUM] Integrate Compute into the Roadmap: Mandate that infrastructure choices are dictated by the specific computational demands of the AI models (e.g., model size, inference latency requirements), not by current hardware availability. (Owner: CTO, Due: TBD)
- [ ] [MEDIUM] Establish a Clear Threshold for Ownership: Only consider purchasing dedicated assets when usage patterns become highly predictable, existing on-premises infrastructure becomes cost-prohibitive, or proprietary, non-standard hardware optimizations are absolutely required for competitive advantage. (Owner: CTO, Due: TBD)
- [ ] [MEDIUM] Focus on FinOps Maturity: Invest heavily in Cloud Engineering (Matthew Wilson's domain) to master cost management, right-sizing instances, and predicting future consumption costs before committing to large asset purchases. (Owner: CTO, Due: TBD)
- [ ] [MEDIUM] Adopt a Hybrid Infrastructure Strategy: Utilize leasing for initial scaling and rapid feature rollout (MVP phase) to maximize cash flow for Series A, while strategically purchasing long-term contracts for core, high-volume proprietary model training infrastructure to establish a defensible technical moat. (Owner: CMO, Due: TBD)
- [ ] [MEDIUM] Develop Segment-Specific Value Metrics: Create distinct ROI calculations for leasing vs. buying tailored to our segments (e.g., banks prioritize operational stability and compliance risk mitigation; hedge funds prioritize speed of analysis). (Owner: CMO, Due: TBD)
- [ ] [MEDIUM] Position Infrastructure as a Differentiator: Market our ability to deliver 'real-time, compliant' AI solutions powered by flexible infrastructure, directly linking hardware choice to superior financial outcomes. (Owner: CMO, Due: TBD)
- [ ] [MEDIUM] Align with Case Study Lessons: Follow the Stripe example—invest in foundational infrastructure that creates a moat before aggressive scaling—to ensure technical leadership precedes market dominance. (Owner: CMO, Due: TBD)
